rows.LABEL: Data Source
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The data source, where these objects are stored. If an object has no data source, it can only be used at runtime (e.g. in an input data sheet for an action), but cannot be saved or read.

rows.LABEL: Attribute
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The attribute name will be used as default caption for most widgets: table columns, fillters, inputs, etc.

rows.LABEL: Alias
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The alias is used to identify the attribute in UXON. Alias are case sensitive and may contain letters, digits and underscores.

rows.LABEL: Data Address
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: This address tells the data source of the object where to find this attribute: e.g. the SELECT statement for SQL  sources, the JSON-path for JSON sources, etc.

rows.LABEL: Object
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The object this attribute belongs to

rows.LABEL: Formatter
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: A formula to format the attribute's value: e.g. =PRICE(VALUE)

rows.LABEL: Default Display Position
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, this attribute will be used to create default tabular representations of the object: e.g. for default columns in a ComboTable widget.

rows.LABEL: Object Label
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, the attribute will be used as label for the object: in all kinds of selecting widgets, in messages, etc.

rows.LABEL: Object UID
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, this attribute will be used to identify the instances of the object. Typically this is some kind of primary key. There may only be one UID-attribute per object.

rows.LABEL: Hidden
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, the attribute will not be displayed in automatically generated widgets

rows.LABEL: Editable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, the value of this attribute in it's data source will be editable.

rows.LABEL: Required
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, the attribute must be assigned a value when creating the object it belongs to.

rows.LABEL: Relation to
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The object the relation points to, if this attribute is a relation

rows.LABEL: Custom Connection
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Overrides the default data connection for this installation only.

rows.LABEL: Default Sorter Position
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, the attribute will be used for sorting in lists of it's object by default. The number specifies the importance of this attribute among other sorting attributes: the list will be sorted by the attribute with a 1 first, the by the attribute wit

rows.LABEL: Default Sorter Direction
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Which way to sort this attribute by default. If not set, the default sorting direction of the data type will be used.

rows.LABEL: Alias
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Unique alias of the app: e.g. "exface.Core"

rows.LABEL: App
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Name of the app

rows.LABEL: App
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Zuordnung des Meta-Objektes zu einer App. Anders als Quellsyteme, stehen Apps für fachliche Anwendungsgebiete. Eine App kann mehrere Quellsysteme umfassen und umgekehrt.

rows.LABEL: Relation to (attribute)
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, the relation will point to the specified attribute instead of the UID of the related object

rows.LABEL: Description
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The description is used for hint texts like this one.

rows.LABEL: Description
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Used for hints and contextual help

rows.LABEL: Base Object
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, any object from this source will inherit from the base object.

rows.LABEL: Extends Object
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Extending an another object will make this object inherit all properties, attributes, actions, behaviors, etc. They can be overridden by defining the a property with the same ALIAS for this object.

rows.LABEL: Configuration
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Configuration options for the data connector to be used in this connection: e.g. username, server address, etc. Refer to the description of the data connector for a list of possible options.

rows.LABEL: Data Source Settings
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Custom settings for the specified data source

rows.LABEL: Data Address Settings
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Custom configuration for the data source of this attribute

rows.LABEL: Default Value
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: This expression will be used when no other value is given (e.g. inputs will be prefilled with this value). You can use attribute aliases, formulas or explicit values (the latter enclosed in quotes!)

rows.LABEL: Fixed Value
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: This expression will allways be evaluated, when the object is saved - eventually overwriting user input. This is handy for attributes like last_update_time, where a fixed value =NOW() will automatically set the attribute to the time of saving.

rows.LABEL: Read-Only
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If set, makes writing to this connection impossible

rows.LABEL: Alias
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The alias of a connection can be used to force a widget to use this specific connection instead of the one specified in the data source.

rows.LABEL: Filter Context
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: UXON description of one or more filter conditions to be set in the application context every time this connection is used. This is usefull for multi-client databases (distinguished by a client_id column), etc.

rows.LABEL: Default Editor
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Widget to be used as an editor for instances of this object by default

rows.LABEL: Object
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Name of the meta object

rows.LABEL: Alias
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The alias of the object is particularly important as it is used to bind a widget to the object in UXON. In uxon the object alias will always be prefixed by the app alias: e.g.  "My.App.MyObject" for an object with the alias "MyObject" within the app

rows.LABEL: Data Address
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: This address tells the data source where to find instances of the object: e.g. a table name for SQL sources, a file name for file sources, an URL for HTML/JSON/XML sources, etc

rows.LABEL: User
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Reference to the owner of the credentials set (ExFace user)

rows.LABEL: Data Connector Configuration
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Set of connector options that will override the default connector config if this user is logged on

rows.LABEL: Name
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Bezeichnung des Quellsystems

rows.LABEL: App
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Optional relation to a specific app. If set, this connection will be part of the app's package. It can still be used in any other app too.

rows.LABEL: App
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Optional relation to a specific app. If set, this data source will be part of the app's package. It can still be used in any other app too.

rows.LABEL: Package
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Reference to the installed package

rows.LABEL: Name
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: File name (without extension!)

rows.LABEL: Relative Path
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: File path relative to the base installation folder including the full filename

rows.LABEL: Folder
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Folder path relative to the base installation folder

rows.LABEL: Filename
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Full file name including extension

rows.LABEL: PHP Class
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Class name with namespace

rows.LABEL: Error Code
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Unique error code. Leave blank to generate an error code automatically.

rows.LABEL: Alias
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Unique id of the action within it's app. The action can be referenced by prefixing this alias with the alias of it's app: e.g. "exface.Core.MyAction" for an action of the core app aliased "MyAction".

rows.LABEL: Name
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Used as caption for buttons. Leave empty to use the default caption of the action.

rows.LABEL: Action App
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The app, this action belongs to. Not necessarily the same as the app of the object!

rows.LABEL: Default Connection
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The default connection is part of the app's metamodel and is maintained by the author of the app. In contrast to CUSTOM_CONNECTION, it will be overwritten by updates.

rows.LABEL: Connection
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The data connection, that is currently used for this data source.

rows.LABEL: Default Query Builder
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The default query builder is maintained by the developer of the app containing the data source and may be overridden by the custom query builder for a specific installation.

rows.LABEL: Custom Query Builder
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The custom query builder overrides the default one for a specific installation. It will not get overwritten when the app of the data source is updated.

rows.LABEL: Value List Delimiter
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Used to separate values of this attribute in concatenaded strings. Change it to a character, that is unlikely to be a regular part of the value if your values will contain commas.

rows.LABEL: Readable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If disabled, the attribute will be ignored when reading the object from the data source. It can still be used for filtering, sorting or even writing. A typical example are parameter-attributes of objects based on SQL procedures or similar. They may n

rows.LABEL: Writable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If disabled, the attribute will be ignored in write-operations even if it is editable: e.g. a calculated attribute or one used for calculation.

rows.LABEL: Readable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If disabled, no read-operations on the data source will be possible with this object: e.g. for a one-way webservice.

rows.LABEL: Writable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If disabled, no write-operations on the data source will be possible with this object: e.g. for a DB view.

rows.LABEL: Readable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If disabled, no read-operations will be possible on this data source (e.g. for a one-way webservice)

rows.LABEL: Writable
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If disabled, no write-operations will be possible on this data source (e.g. a read-only DB)

rows.LABEL: Validation Error Code
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: This error code will be used for all validation errors. Define a custom error to explain users, how values of this data type should look like.

rows.LABEL: Default Editor
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If defined, autogenerated editor widgets for this attribute will use this UXON configuration. Otherwise the default editor of the data type will be used.

rows.LABEL: PHP Class Name
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Class name without namespace

rows.LABEL: Entity
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Name of the UXON entity

rows.LABEL: Default Language
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Default language used in the metamodel and the pages of this app

rows.LABEL: Object Data Address Mask
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Specify a address mask compatible with the used model builder to import only objects from data addresses matching the mask. E.g. the mask "MYPREFIX_%" will specified for an SQL model builder will create objects from all tables or views starting with
